populus per tribus, sc. ‘dispositu8,’ ‘ marshalled in their tribes,' perhaps at or near the ‘septa’ in the Campus. The people were thus formed to meet Nero (14. 13, 2). The tribes were a more select body than the ‘plebs urbana ’ (In- trod. vii. p. 89).

13. solum Augusti sanguinem. The younger Julia and her children (see In· trod. ix. notes 7, 10) are ignored, the only point being the invidious contrast to Tiberius.
